com.k2.Expressions.predicate

Interface Predicate

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Expression<java.lang.Boolean>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractPredicate, PredicateAnd, PredicateBetween, PredicateEquals, PredicateFalse, PredicateGE, PredicateGreaterThan, PredicateGreaterThanOrEqualTo, PredicateGT, PredicateIn, PredicateIsFalse, PredicateIsTrue, PredicateLE, PredicateLessThan, PredicateLessThanOrEqualTo, PredicateLike, PredicateLT, PredicateNot, PredicateNotNull, PredicateNull, PredicateOr, PredicateTrue

    public interface Predicate
extends Expression<java.lang.Boolean>
    The predicate interface extends the Expression interface for Boolean data type. The compound predicates And and Or can contain other predicates and as such from a hierarchical assembly of predicates.
    Author:
    simon
